const v14ReadA={id:"v14-read-a",kind:"passage",label:"Passage for Items 69-72",title:"Coastal Evacuation Map",description:"A coastal municipality printed evacuation maps showing routes to three elevated shelters. During a drill, residents near the market reached a shelter quickly, but families in two narrow streets followed an outdated footpath blocked by a new fence. Mapping staff walked every route with residents, added landmark-based directions, and dated each revision. A second drill reduced wrong turns, although one shelter became crowded. The municipality then planned to test route capacity and assign alternate shelters before the next storm season.",alt:"Passage about evacuation maps, an outdated blocked path, route verification with residents, clearer dated directions, and a plan to test capacity and alternate shelters."};
const v14ReadB={id:"v14-read-b",kind:"passage",label:"Babasahin para sa Aytem 73-76",title:"Aklatang Naglalakbay",description:"Dumadalaw linggo-linggo ang mobile library sa apat na barangay. Pare-pareho ang oras ng paghinto, ngunit kakaunti ang gumagamit sa barangay na may palengke tuwing umaga. Tinanong ng mga kawani ang mga residente at nalaman nilang kasabay ng iskedyul ang oras ng pamimili at paghahatid. Inilipat nila sa hapon ang pagbisita sa barangay na iyon at nagpadala ng paalala isang araw bago dumating. Dumami ang humihiram, kaya susunod nilang susuriin kung anong uri ng aklat ang madalas hanapin upang maiayos ang laman ng sasakyan.",alt:"Teksto tungkol sa mobile library na binago ang oras sa isang barangay matapos alamin ang gawain ng residente, gumamit ng paalala, at planong suriin ang hinahanap na aklat."};
const v14ReadC={id:"v14-read-c",kind:"passage",label:"Passage for Items 77-80",title:"Public Refill Stations",description:"A city installed water refill stations in parks to reduce single-use bottles. Sensors counted dispensed liters, while maintenance logs recorded filter changes and service interruptions. The busiest station also had the most complaints about weak flow. Technicians found that heavy use shortened the interval between filter replacements. The city changed maintenance schedules according to actual volume rather than a fixed monthly date. Complaints declined, but officials kept laboratory water-quality testing separate from sensor data because volume and flow did not prove safety.",alt:"Passage about refill-station use, weak-flow complaints caused by filter demand, volume-based maintenance, and separate laboratory testing because operational sensors do not establish water safety."};
